# Railway Deployment Configuration
# Deploy this project on Railway by connecting your GitHub repo

# Services:
# 1. PostgreSQL: Managed database (auto-provisioned)
# 2. Redis: Managed cache (auto-provisioned)
# 3. API Server: Node.js container (from Dockerfile)
# 4. Frontend: Static build (from Vite build output)

# Environment Variables to set in Railway dashboard:
# DATABASE_URL (auto-populated by PostgreSQL service)
# REDIS_URL (auto-populated by Redis service)
# JWT_SECRET (generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
# JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
# DAILY_SALT (generate with: openssl rand -base64 16)
# FRONTEND_URL (your Railway frontend domain)
# NODE_ENV=production

# Build steps:
# 1. Connect GitHub repo to Railway
# 2. Add PostgreSQL and Redis services
# 3. Set environment variables
# 4. Deploy - Railway auto-detects Dockerfile and builds
